records.addlTxt:
10:14 AM Defendant Neal J Boldon in court.  Attorney Cassandra A Miller Ms. in court for Neal J Boldon.  Prosecuting attorney Alyssa M. Schaller in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case called for plea and sentencing. 
State places offer on the record. 
Court conducts plea colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1 with the repeater struck.  Court finds defendant guilty. 
Counts 2 & 3 are Dismissed and read in.
State and Defense make sentencing recommendations. 

Court orders the following:
IMPOSED AND STAYED: 

JAIL:  12 MONTHS - Straight-time.
3  Days Credit.

TERM ON PROBATION:  18 MONTHS; 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Absolute Sobriety; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*Not to use or possess any synthetic drugs or CBD products;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*Maintain full-time employment;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed;

CONDITION TIME: 90 DAYS, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  

BUY MONEY:  $280;  to City of Waukesha Narcotic and Vice Unit;
COSTS:  $268
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $250 
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
**Cash Bond is reinstated and may be applied to costs/fine/surcharges in this case. The balance is to be paid as a Condition of Probation.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
Court quashes the warrant. 
Signature Bond is reinstated.
The Trial is removed from the calendar.
